AB  - This paper models and analyzes the effects of uncertainties about restriction on profit repatriation and exchange control faced by the multinational enterprise in the host country on its international investment, trade and sales. The former uncertainty constrains investment in the host country. Its effects on exports to the host country and sales there depend on transfer pricing by the multinational enterprise. By contrast, the threat of exchange control on overall exchange transactions is neutral with respect to international investment, but it decreases exports and sales in the host country, and hence are detrimental to its consumers.
